Japan's Anti-DPRK and Anti-Chongryon Moves under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 7 (KCNA) -- Right-wing gangsters of Japan committed such a grave provocation as swarming to a port where ship Mangyongbong-92 was expected to enter on Sept. 4 and hurling abuses at the ship after its arrival and defaming the DPRK flag.
 Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary dismisses this as a very serious provocation in the history of the DPRK-Japan relations as it discloses to the world what a dangerous phase the Japanese reactionaries' hostility and confrontation with the DPRK and the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) have reached. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The commentary continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We can never remain a mere onlooker to the frantic anti-DPRK and anti-Chongryon provocations committed in Japan as they are getting intolerable despite the repeated warnings of the DPRK and Chongryon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The recent incident was also committed at the tacit connivance of the Japanese authorities as was the case with all other previous incidents. The recent incident brought into bolder relief the Japanese reactionaries' vicious and sinister aim to deliberately and systematically foster rowdyism of right-wing gangsters under the pretext of "people's sentiment" and thus fan up the atmosphere of enmity towards the DPRK in the Japanese society and pursue the confrontation with it to the last. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese authorities can never evade the responsibility for the recent serious anti-DPRK provocation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese authorities should bear full responsibility for all the consequences to be entailed by its provocative anti-DPRK and anti-Chongryon moves and thoroughly probe the truth behind the provocation, punish those responsible for it and take an immediate measure to prevent the recurrence of such incident. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will closely follow the Japanese reactionaries' future action.

Foreigners and Overseas Compatriots Arrive 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 7 (KCNA) -- Congratulatory groups of the General Association of Koreans in China led by Chairman Yang Yong Dong, the Federation of Koreans in the U.S. headed by Chairman Ham Song Guk, the Federation of Koreans in Canada headed by Jong Hak Phil, chairman of the Canada Regional Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification, the Federation of Koreans in Australia led by Chairman Rim Yong Mo, and the International Institute of the Juche Idea led by Director General Vishwanath arrived here on Saturday on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Also arriving were a delegation of the Central Control Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon), a delegation of the headquarters chairwomen of the Union of Democratic Korean Women in Japan, a delegation of Chongryon officials, a delegation of officials of the Chongryon Educational Association, a delegation of the Korean Youth in Japan, a home-visiting group of Koreans in Japan, a delegation of organizational workers of the General Association of Koreans in China, a delegation of the Federation of Korean National Economic Workers in China, Ri Jun Sik, delegate of the Society for Cooperation among Koreans in Germany, and Han Chun Hui, widow of Choe Hong Hui, and her party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also arriving were a delegation of the Denmark-DPRK Friendship Association, friendship delegations of Switzerland and Philippines, the chairman of the Luxembourg-Korea Friendship Association, a delegation of the Japanese Women's Liaison Council for Solidarity with the Korean Women, He Hongzhang, president of the Hong Kong Hotung Eric and his party, a delegation of the Loxley Pacific Company Limited of Thailand, and a family of Hu Zhenyi, who was related to the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle and widow of Chai Shiying, a Chinese anti-Japanese revolutionary martyr, and a family of Kim Son, who was related to the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A family of So Sun Ok, an anti-Japanese revolutionary fighter in China and a friendship delegation of Australia arrived here earlier.

Homage Paid to Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 7 (KCNA) -- A state delegation of Uganda led by Vice-President Bukenya Gilbert Balibaseka visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace on September 7 to pay homage to President Kim Il Sung on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the DPRKï¿½D
 It was accompanied by Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, and officials concerned.
 The guests bowed in boundless reverence to Kim Il Sung who lies in state for perpetuity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then they looked round the orders, medals and certificates of honorary titles of the DPRK and foreign countries the President received, the Mourning Hall reminding visitors of those days when the Korean people deeply grieved over the greatest loss of the nation, a train he used during his on-site guidance and foreign visits and a car he used in the last period of his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Ugandan vice-president wrote in the visitor's book that the delegation visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace with the deep reverence of the president and people of Uganda for the President, the father of the people who lies in state for perpetuity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He also wrote that the Ugandan people together with the Korean people will always hold Kim Il Sung in high esteem and his great revolutionary exploits will shine forever.

Talks between Vice-Presidents of DPRK and Uganda
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 7 (KCNA) -- Talks between Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, and Bukenya Gilbert Balibaseka, vice-president of Uganda, were held at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today.
 At the talks both sides exchanged views on further developing the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries and a series of matters of mutual concern. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the talks were officials concerned from the DPRK side and members of the state delegation from the Ugandan side. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks proceeded in a friendly atmosphere.

National Association of Koreans in Australia Issues Statement
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 6 (KCNA) -- The National Association of Koreans in Australia made public a statement on Sept. 2 in support of a joint appeal to scholars of the north, the south and overseas and all the fellow countrymen issued at the inter-Korean seminar on correctly spelling the English name of the country.
 The statement said that correcting the English name of the country misspelt by the Japanese imperialists is not a mere linguistic matter of correcting the name but an important task of the nation to restore the national dignity and sovereignty once ruthlessly trampled down by the Japanese imperialists and glorify them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement fully supported and approved the appeal, noting that correctly spelling the name is aimed to eradicate the leftover of the past colonial rule of the Japanese imperialists and demonstrate to the world that the Korean nation is an upright nation, which highly values the dignity and sovereignty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement stressed that the Koreans in Australia also would conduct a positive campaign to correctly spell the English name of the country.

DPRK Cabinet Hosts Reception
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 6 (KCNA) -- The Cabinet of the DPRK hosted a reception at the People's Palace of Culture on Sept. 5 in honor of the delegation of the DPRK Student Sports Association that had participated in the 22nd Universiad.
 Kwak Pom Gi, vice-premier of the Cabinet, in a speech made at the reception said that the delegation took part in matches with the faith and pluck to win victory given by leader Kim Jong Il despite the ultra-right conservative forces' evermore pronounced anti-DPRK and anti-reunification moves and let the whole of south Korea seethe with strong enthusiasm for reunification, flying flags of the DPRK.
 He made a particular mention of the DPRK women soccer players who won a spectacular success rare in the world history of soccer games by beating all rival teams without losing a single goal and thus demonstrated to the world once again the might of Songun Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the Universiad the delegation displayed to the full the spirit and the might of Juche Korea and greatly helped demonstrate to the world the Koreans' faith and will to achieve the country's reunification at an early date under the banner of the historic June 15 joint declaration. This was a brilliant victory won by the great Songun idea and a striking manifestation of the validity and the vitality of the joint declaration and the Juche-oriented sports policy of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jon Kuk Man, who led the delegation to the Universiad, in a speech said that during the 10-odd days of their stay in Taegu all the members of the delegation deeply cherished the faith that they are sure to triumph as they are led by Kim Jong Il and called upon all of them to uphold him in high esteem forever and become vanguard fighters in devotedly defending him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, officials concerned, the players and supporters' groups and members of the press corps.

Korean People's Strong Desire for Reunification
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 6 (KCNA) -- The Korean people fully demonstrated their strong desire for reunification once again through the 22nd Universiad held in Taegu, south Korea, from August 21 to 31.
 Ultra-right conservatives of south Korea raised a hullabaloo against the Democratic People's Republic of Korea in Seoul on August 15 in an attempt to prevent its participation in the universiad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On August 24 and 26 when the universiad was going on, anti-reunification forces were engaged in insidious activities to hurt the dignity of the DPRK and obstruct its participation in the games. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But the universiad was successfully held and the nation's ardent aspiration after reunification was elevated thanks to the DPRK's magnanimity and patriotic decision to promote national reconciliation and independent reunification with the concerted efforts of the Korean people in the north and the south. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The athletes of the north and the south marched together in the opening ceremony with the Korean peninsula flag in their van amid the playing of the song "Arirang". They demonstrated to the world that the Korean people are the same nation with the same blood, language and culture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The brisk activities of the students' cheering group from the DPRK stirred the nation's desire for reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The venues of the games were rocked by the cheering groups of the north and the south shouting in chorus "We are one," "National reunification," etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They enthusiastically cheered the athletes of the north and the south, waving Korean peninsula flags. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A grand north-south joint art performance for national reconciliation and peace was given in Taegu on August 29 in an atmosphere overflowing with warm compatriotic feelings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The facts show that no matter how desperately the ultra-right conservatives of south Korea may try, can they never hold in check the desire of the nation for reunification.

Meeting of Heroes and Heroines Closes
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 6 (KCNA) -- The meeting of heroes and heroines in the Songun era closed today.
 More speeches were made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers said that the army and the people of the DPRK have performed heroic feats on behalf of the country and the revolution by displaying the transparent spirit of devotedly defending the leader and the spirit of patriotic devotion in the sacred struggle of the Korean revolution that was pioneered with arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There emerged a contingent of heroes and heroines who have performed outstanding feats on behalf of the Party, the leader, the country and the people and the unparalleled spirit of devotion and popular heroism are fully displayed today, they said, adding that
this is a striking manifestation of the tremendous vitality of the great Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They evinced their firm pledge to take the lead in the struggle to defend socialism and build a great prosperous powerful nation in hearty response to the militant call of the WPK "Let us all perform heroic feats to glorify the Songun era!" and thus accomplish the Songun revolutionary cause of the Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An appeal of the meeting to the KPA servicemen and the people was adopted there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal called for fervently following the Songun idea and firmly protecting the Songun polities and thoroughly implementing the Songun line true to the WPK's Songun revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will mark the 60th anniversary of the glorious WPK and the country's liberation in 2005, the appeal noted, calling on all the army and the people to launch a final charge on all fronts of the revolution and construction with high enthusiasm and ardent patriotism, become honorable victors and perform heroic feats and thus proudly celebrate those anniversaries.
